# AI Control Plane - Systemd Environment File Example
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: Example environment file for systemd-managed AI Control Plane
# Usage:   Copy this file to your systemd environment location and populate
#          with actual values:
#
#            cp ai-control-plane.env.example /etc/ai-control-plane/env
#
#          Then edit /etc/ai-control-plane/env with your actual secrets.
#
# Security Warning:
#   - This example file is safe to commit (contains no real secrets)
#   - The actual environment file SHOULD NOT be kept in /etc/ unless your
#     host security policy allows it (root-only readable recommended)
#   - Consider using a secrets manager (HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager,
#     etc.) and sourcing secrets at runtime for production deployments
#
# Canonical Runtime Environment:
#   The canonical runtime environment file remains at demo/.env in the
#   repository. This systemd environment file is an alternative for
#   production deployments where the service runs outside the repository.
#
# See Also:
#   - demo/.env.example for full environment variable reference
#   - docs/deployment/SINGLE_TENANT_PRODUCTION_CONTRACT.md for production
#     deployment requirements and security best practices
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED: LiteLLM Master Key
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: Admin authentication key used to generate per-tool virtual keys
# Required: Yes - LiteLLM will not start without this
# Format: ~64-character string (48 bytes base64-encoded, '=' padding removed)
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 48 | tr -d '\n='
# SECURITY: This key controls admin access to the gateway. Keep it secret.
LITELLM_MASTER_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED: LiteLLM Salt Key
# =============================================================================
# Purpose: Persistent salt for encrypting virtual keys and sensitive data
# Required: Yes - Required for key encryption features
# Format: ~64-character string (48 bytes base64-encoded, '=' padding removed)
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 48 | tr -d '\n='
# SECURITY: Treat as persistent secret. Regenerating invalidates encrypted data.
LITELLM_SALT_KEY=
